issue.title: Add flashy combo animations on consecutive matches
issue.body:
### 📝 User Story  
> As a player, I want visual feedback for streaks of quick matches, so that I feel a sense of momentum.

---

### 💡 Description:

- Track consecutive matches made within a 3-second window.
- For 2+ in a row, play a CSS animation (e.g. particle burst) and show “Combo x2,” “Combo x3,” etc. near the score.
- Reset combo counter after 3s of no match.

---

### ✅ Acceptance Criteria  
1. [ ] Streak counter increments on each match within 3s.
2. [ ] Appropriate animation and label appear for each combo level.
3. [ ] Streak resets after timeout.

---

### ⏱ Estimate  
`[4 h]`

pull_request.title: camera: move main shifting functions to TRX
pull_request.body:
#### Checklist

- [x] I have read the [coding conventions](https://github.com/LostArtefacts/TRX/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#coding-conventions)
- [x] I have added a changelog entry about what my pull request accomplishes, or it is an internal change
- [x] I have added a readme entry about my new feature or OG bug fix, or it is a different change

#### Description

This moves most of the camera shifting/clamping logic to TRX. I've aimed to make the shifting logic in `Camera_ShiftClamp` a bit more concise and readable using macros, as the two games are quite different in this regard. The commits are separated for clarity.

Testing wise, general behaviour can be checked, but there are specific things to look out for, like the starting camera in Folly/Atlantis and the TR1 behaviour when Lara's pulling a switch in a tight space (like the first one in Caves). It looks OK to me but as always, I'd appreciate a second opinion.

I'll continue with the merger incrementally by function group like this to hopefully avoid major problems.

pull_request.title: Add missing POSIX sig2str(3) & str2sig(3) calls
pull_request.body:
Add `sig2str(3)` & `str2sig(3)` calls defined in POSIX 1003.1-2024:
- https://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9799919799/functions/sig2str.html

Also add needed `SIG2STR_MAX` definition:
- https://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9799919799/basedefs/signal.h.html

Alternative implementations:
- Illumos:: https://github.com/illumos/illumos-gate/blob/master/usr/src/lib/libc/port/gen/str2sig.c
- Gnulib: https://github.com/coreutils/gnulib/blob/master/lib/sig2str.c

Notes:
- Had to remove a smaller definition for `SIG2STR_MAX` [here](https://github.com/freebsd/freebsd-src/blob/main/lib/libproc/libproc.h#L108) to use `32` as [defined by Illumos](https://github.com/illumos/illumos-gate/blob/master/usr/src/head/signal.h#L95)
- I avoided sprintf calls using the same approach used in [strsignal.c](https://github.com/freebsd/freebsd-src/blob/main/lib/libc/string/strsignal.c#L124)

Next steps could be:
- Modifying `kill`, `fuser` and other tools that need translation between signal names & numbers.
- Add POSIX definition for `NSIG_MAX` in `<limits.h>` to match `NSIG`.

Fixes https://bugs.freebsd.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=286714
